{"title_page": "Namrata Shrestha", "text_new": "{{short description|Nepalese actress}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Namrataa Shrestha\n| image              = \n| native_name        = \n| birth_name         = Namrata Shrestha\n| birth_date         = 14 June 1986.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://biographytalk.com/namrata-shrestha/|title=Archived copy|access-date=31 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191121144401/https://biographytalk.com/namrata-shrestha/|archive-date=21 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| birth_place        = [[Kathmandu, Nepal]]\n| nationality        = [[Nepalis|Nepalese]]\n| occupation         = Actress, Film Maker\n| years_active       = 2005 &nbsp;\u2013 present\n| height             = \n| website            = https://namrataashrestha.com\n}}\n'''Namrata Shrestha''' is a prolific Nepali Actor. She debuted with Alok Nembang's Sano Sansar in 2008, which was a watershed moment in the Nepali movie industry, ushering in the era of digital cinema and modern urban storytelling.\n\n==Career==\nIn 2008, Shrestha debuted as a film actress in [[Alok Nembang]]'s directional debut [[romantic comedy]] ''[[Sano Sansar]]'', where she starred alongside [[Karma Shakya]] in his debut, [[Jiwan Luitel]] and [[Neer Shah]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.kantipuronline.com/kolnews.php?&nid=160440|title=eKantipur.com - Nepal's No.1 News Portal|last=|first=|date=22 September 2008|website=eKantipur|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080922194015/http://www.kantipuronline.com/kolnews.php?&nid=160440|archive-date=22 September 2008|access-date=19 November 2019}}</ref> The film follows Ravi (played by [[Karma Shakya]]) and Reetu (played by Shrestha) whom are good friends online; however both have clue about that they hate each other in the [[real life]].<ref name=\":0\" /> The film was influenced by 2001 Korean film ''[[My Sassy Girl]]'' and 1998 American film ''[[You've Got Mail]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://filmsofnepal.com/nepali-film-sano-sansar-2008/|title=Nepali Film \u2013 Sano Sansar (2008)|date=1 February 2013|website=Films of Nepal|language=en-US|access-date=19 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191119185521/https://filmsofnepal.com/nepali-film-sano-sansar-2008/|archive-date=19 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In an interview she revealed that \"I did ''Sano Sansar'', my first movie, without any training, and I have come a long way\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tnm.com.np/two-worlds-collide-the-beauty-takes-on-the-beast/|title=TWO WORLDS COLLIDE: THE BEAUTY TAKES ON THE BEAST|website=TNM|language=en-US|access-date=19 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191119190651/http://tnm.com.np/two-worlds-collide-the-beauty-takes-on-the-beast/|archive-date=19 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, Shrestha appeared in two movies. She had a cameo in the film ''[[First Love (2010 Nepali film)|First Love]]'' and as a sponsor in a short film for ''HIV Aids Awareness''. Later that year she debuted in her first theater performance, ''Jalpari''.<ref>[http://www.cybersansar.com/article.php?aid=3186 CS : CyberSansar.com \u2013 Catch Namrata Shrestha as Jalpari] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090528212300/http://www.cybersansar.com/article.php?aid=3186 |date=28 May 2009 }}. CyberSansar.com (21 May 2009). Retrieveas d on 2017-06-24.</ref> \n\nIn 2011, she acted as the main character Carol in the theater production of [[Oleanna (play)|Oleanna]].{{citation needed|date=July 2018}}\n \nIn 2013, she appeared in the Nepali movie ''Chhadke'' alongside [[Saugat Malla]], Daya Hang Rai and Robin Tamang. ''Chhadke'', directed by debutant Nigam Shrestha, got mixed to negative reviews, though overall the movie was commercially successful. Shrestha played the character Soli, an aggressive young woman involved in a local gang.{{citation needed|date=July 2018}}\n \nIn September 2013, ''Maun'' was released, in which both main characters, including Shrestha's, are deaf and mute girl who was a very colorful character and brought that role to life without dialogue. Shrestha had training in sign language.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://xnepali.net/movies/nepali-movie-maun/|title=Nepali movie maun|publisher=Xnepali.net|access-date=14 June 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150702200618/http://xnepali.net/movies/nepali-movie-maun/|archive-date=2 July 2015|url-status=live}}</ref>\n \nIn 2014, Shrestha was cast alongside [[Aaryan Sigdel]] as the onscreen couple for the blockbuster film [[November Rain (2014 film)|November Rain]].\n\nIn 2015, Shrestha starred in the film ''Soul Sister''. Shrestha played a dual character in the film, and sang the Nepali hitsong \"Bistarai Bistarai\". Her singing was much acclaimed.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://xnepali.net/movies/soul-sister-flopped-namrata-shrestha-is-not-sad/|title = Soul sister flopped, namrata is not sad|publisher = Xnepali.net|access-date = 16 August 2015|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150716001842/http://xnepali.net/movies/soul-sister-flopped-namrata-shrestha-is-not-sad/|archive-date = 16 July 2015|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Shrestha starred in the movie ''[[Classic (film)|Classic]]'', again alongside [[Aaryan Sigdel|Aryan Sigdel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cinelahar.com/archives/39795 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=13 June 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151203061856/http://cinelahar.com/archives/39795 |archivedate=3 December 2015 }}</ref> Her role in this movie Classic, marked the apex of her still-growing silver-screen career, having secured each and every award in the best female actor category that year, including the National Award, which was personally bestowed upon her by the President of Nepal.\n\nIn 2018, Shrestha starred in the movie [[Prasad (2018 film)|Prasad]]. she learned the \u201cPaschimey\u201d accent of the character Narayani. \n\nIn 2019, Shrestha starred in the movie Xira, which was her first action movie where she did all stunts on her own and even had to shaved her hair for the role. She wanted it to be a movement for youth to be a stronger and better version of themselves and it was empowering.\n\nTrue to her craft, Shrestha also lends her acting prowess to the Stage. Being flawless in both Nepali and English, her plays Lady by the Sea (2009), [[Oleanna (play)|Oleana]] (2011), [[Yerma]] (2014) and [[Golden Boy (play)|Golden Boy]] (2017) have cemented her reputation as an acting juggernought. \n\nApart from being an actress, Shrestha is also an RJ, an Entrepreneur, Filmmaker and an accomplished Singer. She has released two cover songs - Bistarai Bistarai (OST Soul Sister 2015) and Prakriti ko Sundar Shristi (OST [[Classic (film)|Classic 2016]]).\n\n==Filmography==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Sano Sansar (film)|Sano Sansar]] ''\n| Reetu\n|\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Mero Euta Saathi Cha]]''\n| Shika\n|\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[First Love (2010 Nepali film)|First Love]] ''\n| Guest Appearance\n|\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''HIV Aids Awareness''\n|\n| Short film<ref>{{YouTube|ercmdTysqUk}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Miss U]]''<ref>http://www.nepalichalchitra.com/ {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321211739/http://nepalichalchitra.com/ |date=21 March 2015 }} Miss U's Official Website</ref>\n|  Jasmine\n|\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Chhadke]] ''\n| Soli\n|\n|-\n| 2013\n|''Maun''\n| Barsha\n|\n|-\n| 2014\n|''Megha''\n| Megha\n|\n|-\n| 2014\n|''[[November Rain (2014 film)|November Rain]]''\n| Sheetal\n|\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Tandav (Nepali Movie)|Tandav]]''\n|Maya\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|''Soul Sister''\n|  Maya\n|\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''Adhakatti''\n| Namrata\n| Special appearance in song \"Hey Namrata\"\n|- \n|2016\n|''[[Classic (film)|Classic]]''\n| Dristi\n|\n|- \n|2016\n|''[[Homework (2016 film)|Homework]]'' \n| Anshu Raymajhi\n|\n|-\n| 2016\n| 