un (film)|Maun]]''\n|{{won}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://xnepali.net/movies/film-award-infa-2014-nominations-full-list-of-nominations/|title=INFA award nomination full list|publisher=Xnepali.net|access-date=6 August 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150723165148/http://xnepali.net/movies/film-award-infa-2014-nominations-full-list-of-nominations/|archive-date=23 July 2015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.khabarsite.net/2014/10/aaryan-namrata-win-top-infa-film-award.html?m=1|title=Aaryan namrata win top infa film award|publisher=khabarsite.net|access-date=6 August 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304025144/http://www.khabarsite.net/2014/10/aaryan-namrata-win-top-infa-film-award.html?m=1|archive-date=4 March 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|2015\n|NEFTA awards 2015\n|Best Actress\n|''[[November Rain (2014 film)|November Rain]]''\n|{{nominated}}<ref name=\"Nepali Movies\" />\n|-\n|2015\n|NEFTA awards\n|Popular Actress of the year\n|''[[November Rain (2014 film)|November Rain]]''\n|{{nominated}}<ref name=\"Nepali Movies\">{{cite web|url=http://xnepali.net/movies/top-5-nomination-nefta-award-2015-full-list/|title=Top 5 nomination nefta award 2015 full list|publisher=xnepali.net|access-date=14 August 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150805000313/http://xnepali.net/movies/top-5-nomination-nefta-award-2015-full-list/|archive-date=5 August 2015|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|FAAN Awards\n|Best Actress \n|''[[Classic (film)|Classic]]''\n|{{won}}<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.moviemandu.com/2016/07/02/pashupati-prasad-wins-4-faan-awards-the-complete-winners-list/|title =PASHUPATI PRASAD Wins 4 FAAN Awards, The Complete Winners List|publisher =moviemandu.com|access-date =7 July 2016|archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20160706085955/http://www.moviemandu.com/2016/07/02/pashupati-prasad-wins-4-faan-awards-the-complete-winners-list/|archive-date =6 July 2016|url-status =dead}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|Dcine awards\n|Best Actress\n|''[[Classic (film)|Classic]]''\n|{{won}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/07/456209/|title='\u0921\u0940 \u0938\u093f\u0928\u0947 \u0905\u0935\u093e\u0930\u094d\u0921'\u092e\u093e '\u0915\u094d\u0932\u093e\u0938\u093f\u0915, \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0947\u092e\u0917\u0940\u0924 \u0930 \u0935\u0921\u093e \u0928\u092e\u094d\u092c\u0930 \u096c'\u0915\u094b \u092c\u0930\u094d\u091a\u0938\u094d\u0935(\u092a\u0942\u0930\u094d\u0923 \u0938\u0942\u091a\u0940\u0938\u0939\u093f\u0924)|publisher=onlinekhabar.com|access-date=14 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816123036/http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/07/456209/|archive-date=16 August 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/08/465821/|title=\u0906\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0928 \u0930 \u0928\u092e\u094d\u0930\u0924\u093e \u092b\u0947\u0930\u093f \u0909\u0924\u094d\u0915\u0943\u0937\u094d\u091f, '\u0915\u094d\u0932\u093e\u0938\u093f\u0915' \u092c\u0930\u094d\u0937\u0915\u0948 \u0909\u0924\u094d\u0915\u0943\u0937\u094d\u091f \u091a\u0932\u091a\u093f\u0924\u094d\u0930(\u092b\u094b\u091f\u093e\u0947 \u092b\u093f\u091a\u0930\u0938\u0939\u093f\u0924)|publisher=onlinekhabar.com|access-date=14 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160815164448/http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/08/465821/|archive-date=15 August 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|NFDC Award 2016 \n|Best actress\n|''[[Classic (film)|Classic]]''\n|{{won}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/08/464400/|title=\u0915\u094d\u0932\u093e\u0938\u093f\u0915 \u0930 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0947\u092e\u0917\u0940\u0924\u0915\u094b \u091a\u0930\u094d\u0915\u094b \u092d\u093f\u0921\u0928\u094d\u0924, '\u092a\u0936\u0941\u092a\u0924\u093f \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0938\u093e\u0926 \u0930 \u0915\u092c\u0921\u094d\u0921\u0940 \u0915\u092c\u0921\u094d\u0921\u0940' \u092a\u0928\u093f \u0915\u092e \u091b\u0948\u0928\u0928\u094d|publisher=onlinekhabar.com|access-date=24 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827073856/http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/08/464400/|archive-date=27 August 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rangakhabar.com/nfdc-award-2073-full-winners-names/|title=\u090f\u0928\u090f\u092b\u0921\u093f\u0938\u0940 \u0905\u0935\u093e\u0930\u094d\u0921\u092e\u093e '\u0915\u094d\u0932\u093e\u0938\u093f\u0915'\u0915\u094b \u0926\u092c\u0926\u092c\u093e ,\u0905\u0935\u093e\u0930\u094d\u0921 \u0925\u093e\u092a\u0947\u092a\u091b\u0940 \u0915\u0947 \u092d\u0928\u0947 \u0924 \u0935\u093f\u091c\u0947\u0924\u093e\u0939\u0930\u0941\u0932\u0947 ? (\u092d\u093f\u0921\u093f\u092f\u094b)|publisher=rangakhabar.com|access-date=23 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923190744/http://www.rangakhabar.com/nfdc-award-2073-full-winners-names/|archive-date=23 September 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|LG Film Awards \n|Best actress\n|''[[Classic (film)|Classic]]''\n|{{won}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/08/472724/|title=\u0921\u0940\u0938\u0940\u0915\u094b \u0905\u0935\u093e\u0930\u094d\u0921\u092e\u093e \u0928\u092e\u094d\u0930\u0924\u093e\u0926\u0947\u0916\u093f \u0938\u093e\u092e\u094d\u0930\u093e\u091c\u094d\u091e\u0940\u0915\u094b \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0924\u093f\u0938\u094d\u092a\u0930\u094d\u0927\u093e, \u092e\u0928\u094b\u0928\u092f\u092e\u093e \u096b \u092b\u093f\u0932\u094d\u092e\u0915\u094b \u0935\u0930\u094d\u091a\u0938\u094d\u0935|publisher=onlinekhabar.com|access-date=31 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160904113956/http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/08/472724/|archive-date=4 September 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/09/475902/|title=\u0928\u092e\u094d\u0930\u0924\u093e \u0930 \u0926\u092f\u093e\u0939\u093e\u0919 \u0909\u0924\u094d\u0915\u0943\u0937\u094d\u091f \u0928\u093e\u092f\u0915\u2013\u0928\u093e\u092f\u093f\u0915\u093e, \u0930\u0947\u0916\u093e \u0930 \u0905\u0928\u092e\u094b\u0932 '\u092a\u092a\u0941\u0932\u0930 \u090f\u0915\u094d\u091f\u0930'|publisher=onlinekhabar.com|access-date=8 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160909141209/http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/09/475902/|archive-date=9 September 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|2019\n|Dcine awards\n|Best Actress\n|''[[Prasad (2018 film)|Prasad]]''\n|{{won}}<ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Namrata Shrestha}}\n* {{IMDb name|4645539}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shrestha, Namrata}}\n[[Category:Nepalese film actresses]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Nepalese female models]]\n[[Category:People from Dharan]]\n[[Category:Nepalese stage actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Nepalese actresses]]\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Nepalese actress}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Namrataa Shrestha\n| image              = \n| native_name        = \n| birth_name         = Namrata Shrestha\n| birth_date         = June 14, 1986.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://biographytalk.com/namrata-shrestha/|title=Archived copy|access-date=2020-03-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191121144401/https://biographytalk.com/namrata-shrestha/|archive-date=2019-11-21|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| birth_place        = [[Kathmandu, Nepal]]\n| nationality        = [[Nepalis|Nepalese]]\n| occupation         = Actress, Film Maker\n| years_active       = 2005 &nbsp;\u2013 present\n| height             = \n| website            = https://namrataashrestha.com\n}}\n'''Namrata Shrestha''' is a prolific Nepali Actor. She debuted with Alok Nembang's Sano Sansar in 2008, which was a watershed moment in the Nepali movie industry, ushering in the era of digital cinema and modern urban storytelling.\n\n==Career==\nIn 2008, Shrestha debuted as a film actress in [[Alok Nembang]]'s directional debut [[romantic comedy]] ''[[Sano Sansar]]'', where she starred alongside [[Karma Shakya]] in his debut, [[Jiwan Luitel]] and [[Neer Shah]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.kantipuronline.com/kolnews.php?&nid=160440|title=eKantipur.com - Nepal's No.1 News Portal|last=|first=|date=2008-09-22|website=eKantipur|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080922194015/http://www.kantipuronline.com/kolnews.php?&nid=160440|archive-date=22 September 2008|access-date=2019-11-19}}</ref> The film follows Ravi (played by [[Karma Shakya]]) and Reetu (played by Shrestha) whom are good friends online; however both have clue about that they hate each other in the [[real life]].<ref name=\":0\" /> The film was influenced by 2001 Korean film ''[[My Sassy Girl]]'' and 1998 American film ''[[You've Got Mail]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://filmsofnepal.com/nepali-film-sano-sansar-2008/|title=Nepali Film \u2013 Sano Sansar (2008)|date=2013-02-01|website=Films of Nepal|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191119185521/https://filmsofnepal.com/nepali-film-sano-sansar-2008/|archive-date=2019-11-19|url-status=live}}</ref> In an interview she revealed that \"I did ''Sano Sansar'', my first movie, without any training, and I have come a long way\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tnm.com.np/two-worlds-collide-the-beauty-takes-on-the-beast/|title=TWO WORLDS COLLIDE: THE BEAUTY TAKES ON THE BEAST|website=TNM|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191119190651/http://tnm.com.np/two-worlds-collide-the-beauty-takes-on-the-beast/|archive-date=2019-11-19|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, Shrestha appeared in two movies. She had a cameo in the film ''[[First Love (2010 Nepali film)|First Love]]'' and as a sponsor in a short film for ''HIV Aids Awareness''. Later that year she debuted in her first theater performance, ''Jalpari''.<ref>[http://www.cybersansar.com/article.php?aid=3186 CS : CyberSansar.com \u2013 Catch Namrata Shrestha as Jalpari] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090528212300/http://www.cybersansar.com/article.php?aid=3186 |date=2009-05-28 }}. CyberSansar.com (2009-05-21). Retrieveas d on 2017-06-24.</ref> \n\nIn 2011, she acted as the main character Carol in the theater production of [[Oleanna (play)|Oleanna]].{{citation needed|date=July 2018}}\n \nIn 2013, she appeared in the Nepali movie ''Chhadke'' alongside [[Saugat Malla]], Daya Hang Rai and Robin Tamang. ''Chhadke'', directed by debutant Nigam Shrestha, got mixed to negative reviews, though overall the movie was commercially successful. Shrestha played the character Soli, an aggressive young woman involved in a local gang.{{citation needed|date=July 2018}}\n \nIn September 2013, ''Maun'' was released, in which both main characters, including Shrestha's, are deaf and mute girl who was a very colorful character and brought that role to life without dialogue. Shrestha had training in sign language.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://xnepali.net/movies/nepali-movie-maun/|title=Nepali movie maun|publisher=Xnepali.net|access-date=2015-06-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150702200618/http://xnepali.net/movies/nepali-movie-maun/|archive-date=2015-07-02|url-status=live}}</ref>\n \nIn 2014, Shrestha was cast alongside [[Aaryan Sigdel]] as the onscreen couple for the blockbuster film [[November Rain (2014 film)|November Rain]].\n\nIn 2015, Shrestha starred in the film ''Soul Sister''. Shrestha played a dual character in the film, and sang the Nepali hitsong \"Bistarai Bistarai\". Her singing was much acclaimed.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://xnepali.net/movies/soul-sister-flopped-namrata-shrestha-is-not-sad/|title = Soul sister flopped, namrata is not sad|publisher = Xnepali.net|access-date = 2015-08-16|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150716001842/http://xnepali.net/movies/soul-sister-flopped-namrata-shrestha-is-not-sad/|archive-date = 2015-07-16|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Shrestha starred in the movie ''[[Classic (film)|Classic]]'', again alongside [[Aaryan Sigdel|Aryan Sigdel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cinelahar.com/archives/39795 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=June 13, 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151203061856/http://cinelahar.com/archives/39795 |archivedate=December 3, 2015 }}</ref> Her role in this movie Classic, marked the apex of her still-growing silver-screen career, having secured each and every award in the best female actor category that year, including the National Award, which was personally bestowed upon her by the President of Nepal.\n\nIn 2018, Shrestha starred in the movie [[Prasad (2018 film)|Prasad]]. she learned the \u201cPaschimey\u201d accent of the character Narayani. \n\nIn 2019, Shrestha starred in the movie Xira, which was her first action movie where she did all stunts on her own and even had to shaved her hair for the role. She wanted it to be a movement for youth to be a stronger and better version of themselves and it was empowering.\n\nTrue to her craft, Shrestha also lends her acting prowess to the Stage. Being flawless in both Nepali and English, her plays Lady by the Sea (2009), [[Oleanna (play)|Oleana]] (2011), [[Yerma]] (2014) and [[Golden Boy (play)|Golden Boy]] (2017) have cemented her reputation as an acting juggernought. \n\nApart from being an actress, Shrestha is also an RJ, an Entrepreneur, Filmmaker and an accomplished Singer. She has released two cover songs - Bistarai Bistarai (OST Soul Sister 2015) and Prakriti ko Sundar Shristi (OST [[Classic (film)|Classic 2016]]).\n\n==Filmography==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Sano Sansar (film)|Sano Sansar]] ''\n| Reetu\n|\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Mero Euta Saathi Cha]]''\n| Shika\n|\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[First Love (2010 Nepali film)|First Love]] ''\n| Guest Appearance\n|\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''HIV Aids Awareness''\n|\n| Short film<ref>{{YouTube|ercmdTysqUk}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Miss U]]''<ref>http://www.nepalichalchitra.com/ {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321211739/http://nepalichalchitra.com/ |date=2015-03-21 }} Miss U's Official Website</ref>\n|  Jasmine\n|\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Chhadke]] ''\n| Soli\n|\n|-\n| 2013\n|''Maun''\n| Barsha\n|\n|-\n| 2014\n|''Megha''\n| Megha\n|\n|-\n| 2014\n|''[[November Rain (2014 film)|November Rain]]''\n| Sheetal\n|\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Tandav (Nepali Movie)|Tandav]]''\n|Maya\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|''Soul Sister''\n|  Maya\n|\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''Adhakatti''\n| Namrata\n| Special appearance in song \"Hey Namrata\"\n|- \n|2016\n|''[[Classic (film)|Classic]]''\n| Dristi\n|\n|- \n|2016\n|''[[Homework (2016 film)|Homework]]'' \n| Anshu Raymajhi\n|\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Sambhodhan]]''\n| Parol\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|[[Parva (2017 film)|Parva]]\n|Reetu\n|\n|-\n|2018\n|[[Prasad (2018 film)|Prasad]]\n|Narayani\n|\n|-\n|2019\n|Xira<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://enepalimovie.com/xira-nepali-movie-trailer/|title=Fierce Namrata in the trailer of XIRA!|last=enepalimovie-team|first=Post Author|date=2019-08-09|website=enepalimovie|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190814031201/https://enepalimovie.com/xira-nepali-movie-trailer/|archive-date=2019-08-14|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|Xira\n|\n|}\n\n==Theatre appearances==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|- \n! Year\n! Film\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''Jalpari''\n| Jalpari \n| Based on the play [[Lady From the Sea]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cybersansar.com/article.php?aid=3186|title=CS : CyberSansar.com \u2013 Catch Namrata Shrestha as Jalpari|accessdate=22 September 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160128102951/http://www.cybersansar.com/article.php?aid=3186|archive-date=28 January 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Oleanna (play)|Oleanna]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://xnepali.net/movies/namrata-to-debut-in-theater-with-oleanna/|title=Namrata to debut in theater with Oleanna|accessdate=22 September 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150220115002/http://xnepali.net/movies/namrata-to-debut-in-theater-with-oleanna/|archive-date=20 February 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n| Carol\n|\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Yerma (play)|Yerma]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://xnepali.net/movies/namrata-to-debut-in-theater-with-yerma/|title=Namrata to debut in theater with Yerma|accessdate=22 September 2014}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n| Yerma\n|\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Golden Boy (play)|Golden Boy]]''\n| Golden Boy\n|\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Awards\n!Category\n!Work\n!Result\n|-\n|2014\n|INFA Awards (Hong Kong)\n|Best Actor (female) 2014\n|''[[Maun (film)|Maun]]''\n|{{won}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://xnepali.net/movies/film-award-infa-2014-nominations-full-list-of-nominations/|title=INFA award nomination full list|publisher=Xnepali.net|access-date=2015-08-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150723165148/http://xnepali.net/movies/film-award-infa-2014-nominations-full-list-of-nominations/|archive-date=2015-07-23|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.khabarsite.net/2014/10/aaryan-namrata-win-top-infa-film-award.html?m=1|title=Aaryan namrata win top infa film award|publisher=khabarsite.net|access-date=2015-08-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304025144/http://www.khabarsite.net/2014/10/aaryan-namrata-win-top-infa-film-award.html?m=1|archive-date=2016-03-04|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|2015\n|NEFTA awards 2015\n|Best Actress\n|''[[November Rain (2014 film)|November Rain]]''\n|{{nominated}}<ref name=\"Nepali Movies\" />\n|-\n|2015\n|NEFTA awards\n|Popular Actress of the year\n|''[[November Rain (2014 film)|November Rain]]''\n|{{nominated}}<ref name=\"Nepali Movies\">{{cite web|url=http://xnepali.net/movies/top-5-nomination-nefta-award-2015-full-list/|title=Top 5 nomination nefta award 2015 full list|publisher=xnepali.net|access-date=2015-08-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150805000313/http://xnepali.net/movies/top-5-nomination-nefta-award-2015-full-list/|archive-date=2015-08-05|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|FAAN Awards\n|Best Actress \n|''[[Classic (film)|Classic]]''\n|{{won}}<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.moviemandu.com/2016/07/02/pashupati-prasad-wins-4-faan-awards-the-complete-winners-list/|title =PASHUPATI PRASAD Wins 4 FAAN Awards, The Complete Winners List|publisher =moviemandu.com|access-date =2016-07-07|archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20160706085955/http://www.moviemandu.com/2016/07/02/pashupati-prasad-wins-4-faan-awards-the-complete-winners-list/|archive-date =2016-07-06|url-status =dead}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|Dcine awards\n|Best Actress\n|''[[Classic (film)|Classic]]''\n|{{won}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/07/456209/|title='\u0921\u0940 \u0938\u093f\u0928\u0947 \u0905\u0935\u093e\u0930\u094d\u0921'\u092e\u093e '\u0915\u094d\u0932\u093e\u0938\u093f\u0915, \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0947\u092e\u0917\u0940\u0924 \u0930 \u0935\u0921\u093e \u0928\u092e\u094d\u092c\u0930 \u096c'\u0915\u094b \u092c\u0930\u094d\u091a\u0938\u094d\u0935(\u092a\u0942\u0930\u094d\u0923 \u0938\u0942\u091a\u0940\u0938\u0939\u093f\u0924)|publisher=onlinekhabar.com|access-date=2016-08-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816123036/http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/07/456209/|archive-date=2016-08-16|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/08/465821/|title=\u0906\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0928 \u0930 \u0928\u092e\u094d\u0930\u0924\u093e \u092b\u0947\u0930\u093f \u0909\u0924\u094d\u0915\u0943\u0937\u094d\u091f, '\u0915\u094d\u0932\u093e\u0938\u093f\u0915' \u092c\u0930\u094d\u0937\u0915\u0948 \u0909\u0924\u094d\u0915\u0943\u0937\u094d\u091f \u091a\u0932\u091a\u093f\u0924\u094d\u0930(\u092b\u094b\u091f\u093e\u0947 \u092b\u093f\u091a\u0930\u0938\u0939\u093f\u0924)|publisher=onlinekhabar.com|access-date=2016-08-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160815164448/http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/08/465821/|archive-date=2016-08-15|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|NFDC Award 2016 \n|Best actress\n|''[[Classic (film)|Classic]]''\n|{{won}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/08/464400/|title=\u0915\u094d\u0932\u093e\u0938\u093f\u0915 \u0930 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0947\u092e\u0917\u0940\u0924\u0915\u094b \u091a\u0930\u094d\u0915\u094b \u092d\u093f\u0921\u0928\u094d\u0924, '\u092a\u0936\u0941\u092a\u0924\u093f \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0938\u093e\u0926 \u0930 \u0915\u092c\u0921\u094d\u0921\u0940 \u0915\u092c\u0921\u094d\u0921\u0940' \u092a\u0928\u093f \u0915\u092e \u091b\u0948\u0928\u0928\u094d|publisher=onlinekhabar.com|access-date=2016-08-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827073856/http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/08/464400/|archive-date=2016-08-27|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rangakhabar.com/nfdc-award-2073-full-winners-names/|title=\u090f\u0928\u090f\u092b\u0921\u093f\u0938\u0940 \u0905\u0935\u093e\u0930\u094d\u0921\u092e\u093e '\u0915\u094d\u0932\u093e\u0938\u093f\u0915'\u0915\u094b \u0926\u092c\u0926\u092c\u093e ,\u0905\u0935\u093e\u0930\u094d\u0921 \u0925\u093e\u092a\u0947\u092a\u091b\u0940 \u0915\u0947 \u092d\u0928\u0947 \u0924 \u0935\u093f\u091c\u0947\u0924\u093e\u0939\u0930\u0941\u0932\u0947 ? (\u092d\u093f\u0921\u093f\u092f\u094b)|publisher=rangakhabar.com|access-date=2016-09-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923190744/http://www.rangakhabar.com/nfdc-award-2073-full-winners-names/|archive-date=2016-09-23|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|LG Film Awards \n|Best actress\n|''[[Classic (film)|Classic]]''\n|{{won}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/08/472724/|title=\u0921\u0940\u0938\u0940\u0915\u094b \u0905\u0935\u093e\u0930\u094d\u0921\u092e\u093e \u0928\u092e\u094d\u0930\u0924\u093e\u0926\u0947\u0916\u093f \u0938\u093e\u092e\u094d\u0930\u093e\u091c\u094d\u091e\u0940\u0915\u094b \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0924\u093f\u0938\u094d\u092a\u0930\u094d\u0927\u093e, \u092e\u0928\u094b\u0928\u092f\u092e\u093e \u096b \u092b\u093f\u0932\u094d\u092e\u0915\u094b \u0935\u0930\u094d\u091a\u0938\u094d\u0935|publisher=onlinekhabar.com|access-date=2016-08-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160904113956/http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/08/472724/|archive-date=2016-09-04|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/09/475902/|title=\u0928\u092e\u094d\u0930\u0924\u093e \u0930 \u0926\u092f\u093e\u0939\u093e\u0919 \u0909\u0924\u094d\u0915\u0943\u0937\u094d\u091f \u0928\u093e\u092f\u0915\u2013\u0928\u093e\u092f\u093f\u0915\u093e, \u0930\u0947\u0916\u093e \u0930 \u0905\u0928\u092e\u094b\u0932 '\u092a\u092a\u0941\u0932\u0930 \u090f\u0915\u094d\u091f\u0930'|publisher=onlinekhabar.com|access-date=2016-09-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160909141209/http://www.onlinekhabar.com/2016/09/475902/|archive-date=2016-09-09|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|2019\n|Dcine awards\n|Best Actress\n|''[[Prasad (2018 film)|Prasad]]''\n|{{won}}<ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Namrata Shrestha}}\n* {{IMDb name|4645539}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shrestha, Namrata}}\n[[Category:Nepalese film actresses]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Nepalese female models]]\n[[Category:People from Dharan]]\n[[Category:Nepalese stage actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Nepalese actresses]]\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n", "name_user": "Robby.is.on", "label": "safe", "comment": "Date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Namrata_Shrestha"}
{"title_page": "Andre Norton", "text_new": "{{Infobox writer\n| name         = Andre Alice Norton\n| image        = \n| imagesize    = \n| alt          = \n| caption      = \n| pseudonym    = Andre Norton<br />Andrew North<br />Allen Weston\n| birth_name   = Alice Mary Norton\n| birth_date   = {{birth date|1912|02|17}}<ref name=\"SSDI\" />\n| birth_place  = [[Cleveland]], [[Ohio]], U.S.\n| death_date   = {{death date and age|2005|03|17|1912|02|17}}\n| death_place  = [[Murfreesboro, Tennessee]], U.S.\n| occupation   = Writer\n| nationality  = American\n| ethnicity    = \n| citizenship  = \n| education    = \n| alma_mater   = \n| period       = 1934\u20132005\n| genre        = [[Science fiction]], [[fantasy]], [[romance novel]]s, [[adventure fiction]]\n| subject      = <!-- nonfiction -->\n| movement     = \n| notableworks = \n| spouse       = \n| partner      = \n| children     = \n| relatives    = \n| influences   = \n| influenced   = \n| awards       = SFWA Grand Master, Science Fiction and Fantasy Hall of Fame\n| signature    = \n| website      = \n| portaldisp   = \n}}\n\n'''Andre Alice Norton''' (born '''Alice Mary Norton''', February 17, 1912&nbsp;&ndash; March 17, 2005) was an [[American people|American]] writer of [[science fiction]] and [[fantasy]], who also wrote works of [[historical fiction]] and contemporary fiction. She wrote primarily under the [[pen name]] '''Andre Norton''', but also under '''Andrew North''' and '''Allen Weston'''. She was the first woman to be [[Gandalf Award|Gandalf Grand Master]] of Fantasy,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2005/03/18/books/andre-norton-dies-at-93-a-master-of-science-fiction.html|title=Andre Norton Dies at 93; a Master of Science Fiction|last=Lehmann-Haupt|first=Christopher|date=2005-03-18|work=The New York Times|access-date=2018-02-04|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> to be [[SFWA Grand Master]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/GrandMaster1984.html|title=SFWA Grand Master Award Listings 1984|last=|first=|date=|website=SFWA Grand Master Award Listings 1984|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20030110115152/http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/GrandMaster1984.html|archive-date=2003-01-10|url-status=dead|access-date=}}</ref> and to be inducted by the [[EMP Museum#Science Fiction Hall of Fame|Science Fiction and Fantasy Hall of Fame]].<ref name=\"SFAwards\" /><ref name=\"SFWA\" /><ref name=\"sfhof-old\" /><!-- source for each first is scanning the list -->\n\n==Biography and career==\n===Biography===\nAlice Mary Norton was born in [[Cleveland, Ohio]] in 1912.<ref>Bankston, John. Andre Norton. New York: Chelsea House, 2010, p. 16.</ref>  Her parents were Adalbert Freely Norton, who owned a rug company, and Bertha Stemm Norton. Alice began writing at Collinwood High School in Cleveland, under the tutelage of Sylvia Cochrane. She was the editor of a literary page in the school's paper,''The Collinwood Spotlight'', for which she wrote short stories. During this time, she wrote her first book, ''Ralestone Luck'', which was eventually published as her second novel in 1938.\n\nAfter graduating from high school in 1930, Norton planned to become a teacher, and began studying at Flora Stone Mather College of [[Case Western Reserve University|Western Reserve University]]. However, in 1932 she had to leave because of the Depression, and began working for the [[Cleveland Public Library|Cleveland Library System]],<ref name=\"Mclellan\" /> where she remained for 18 years, latterly in the children's section of the Nottingham Branch Library in Cleveland. In 1934, she legally changed her name to Andre Alice Norton, a pen name she had adopted for her first book, published later that year, to increase her marketability, since boys were the main audience for fantasy.<ref name=\"Mclellan\" />\n\nDuring 1940\u20131941, she worked as a special librarian in the cataloging department of the [[Library of Congress]].<ref>Bankston, John. Andre Norton. New York: Chelsea House, 2010, p. 50.</ref> She was involved in a project related to alien citizenship which was abruptly terminated upon the American entry into [[World War&nbsp;II]].<!--cn--> In 1941 she bought a bookstore called Mystery House in [[Mount Rainier, Maryland]], the eastern neighbor of [[Washington, D.C.]] The business failed, and she returned to the Cleveland Public Library until 1950, when she retired due to ill health.<ref>{{cite web|author=Steve Holland |url=https://www.theguardian.com/news/2005/mar/29/guardianobituaries.booksobituaries |title=Obituary: Andre Norton &#124; Books |publisher=The Guardian |date=2013-07-06 |accessdate=2013-07-14}}</ref> She then began working as a [[publisher's reader|reader]] for publisher-editor [[Martin Greenberg]]{{efn|[[Martin Greenberg]] is no relation of [[Martin H. Greenberg]] (1941\u20132011)<!-- MHG claimed, we say --> with whom Norton co-edited the ''Catfantastic'' series of five anthologies ([[DAW Books]], 1989 to 1999).}} at [[Gnome Press]], a [[small press]] in New York City that focused on science fiction.<!-- source is our Gnome Press --> She remained until 1958, when, with 21 novels published,<!--publ dates 1934 to 1957--><ref name=\"Lehmannhaupt\" /><ref name=\"kirkus-search\"/> she became a full-time professional writer.\n\nAs Norton's health became uncertain, she moved to Winter Park, Florida in November 1966, where she remained until 1997.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.andre-norton.org/anorton/anbio.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130223162336/http://www.andre-norton.org/anorton/anbio.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=2013-02-23 |title=ANDRE NORTON ORG: Biography of Andre Norton |publisher=Andre-norton.org |date=1912-02-17 |author=Maciej Zaleski-Ejgierd |access-date=2013-07-14 }}</ref>  She moved to [[Murfreesboro, Tennessee]] in 1997 and was under [[hospice care]] from February 21, 2005. She died at home on March 17, 2005, of congestive heart failure.\n\n===Literary career===\n{{For|a full list of Norton's books|Andre Norton bibliography}}\n[[File:Fantasy book 1947 v1 n1.jpg|thumb|right|Norton's novelette \"The People of the Crater\", published under her \"Andrew North\" pseudonym, was the cover story in the debut issue of ''Fantasy Book'' in 1947.]]\n\n[[File:Fantasy book 1948 n3.jpg|thumb|right|\"The Gifts of Asti\", also published under the \"North\" byline, took the cover of the third issue of ''Fantasy Book'' in 1948.]]\n\nIn 1934, her first book, ''The Prince Commands, being sundry adventures of Michael Karl, sometime crown prince & pretender to the throne of Morvania'', with illustrations by [[Kate Seredy]],  was published by [[D. Appleton & Company|D.&nbsp;Appleton\u2013Century Company]] (cataloged by the U.S. Library of Congress as by \"Andr\u00e9 Norton\").<ref name=\"LCC\" /><ref name=\"LCC1\" /> She went on to write several historical novels for the juvenile (now called \"young adult\") market.\n\nNorton's first published science fiction was a [[short story]], \"The People of the Crater\", which appeared under the name \"Andrew North\" as pages 4\u201318 of the inaugural 1947 number of ''Fantasy Book'', a magazine from [[Fantasy Publishing Company, Inc.]]<ref name=\"isfdb\" /><!-- eds. owner [[William L. Crawford]] and Margaret Crawford; eight numbers 1947 to 1951 --> Her first fantasy novel, ''Huon of the Horn'', published by [[Harcourt Brace]] under her own name in 1951, adapted the 13th-century story of [[Huon of Bordeaux|Huon, Duke of Bordeaux]].<ref name=\"isfdb-huon\" /> Her first science fiction novel, ''Star Man's Son, 2250 A.D.'', appeared from Harcourt in 1952.<ref name=\"Locus\" /> She became a prolific novelist in the 1950s, with many of her books published for the juvenile market, at least in their original hardcover editions.\n\nAs of 1958, when she became a full-time professional writer, ''Kirkus'' had reviewed 16 of her novels,{{efn|name=starred}} and awarded four of them starred reviews.<ref name=\"kirkus-search\"/>  Her four starred reviews to 1957 had been awarded for three historical adventure novels\u2014''Follow the Drum'' (1942), ''Scarface'' (1948), ''Yankee Privateer'' (1955)\u2014and one cold war adventure, ''At Swords' Points'' (1954). She received four starred reviews subsequently, latest in 1966, including three for science fiction.<ref name= \"kirkus-search\"/>\n\nNorton was twice nominated for the [[Hugo Award]], in 1964 for the novel ''Witch World'' and in 1967 for the novelette \"Wizard's World\". She was nominated three times for the [[World Fantasy Award]] for lifetime achievement, winning the award in 1998. Norton won a number of other genre awards and regularly had works appear in the ''Locus'' annual \"best of year\" polls.<ref name=\"SFAwards\" />\n\nShe was a founding member of the [[Swordsmen and Sorcerers' Guild of America]] (SAGA), a loose-knit group of [[Heroic fantasy|Heroic Fantasy]] authors founded in the 1960s, led by [[Lin Carter]], with entry by fantasy credentials alone. Norton was the only woman among the original eight members.<!-- source is our SAGA; later 15 inclg 5 women --> Some works by SAGA members were published in [[Lin Carter]]'s ''[[Flashing Swords!]]'' anthologies.\n\nIn 1976, [[Gary Gygax]] invited Norton to play ''[[Dungeons & Dragons]]'' in his [[Greyhawk]] world. Norton subsequently wrote ''Quag Keep'', which involved a group of characters who travel from the real world to Greyhawk. It was the first novel to be set, at least partially, in the Greyhawk setting and, according to ''Alternative Worlds'', the first to be based on ''D&D''.<ref>{{cite book|last=Norton|first=Andre|author2=Jean Rabe|title=Return to Quag Keep |publisher=MacMillan |date=2006 | pages=Introduction | isbn=0-7653-1298-0 | url= https://books.google.com/books?id=zRiBR0YlFJAC&pg=PP3&dq=greyhawk+gygax }}</ref> ''Quag Keep'' was excerpted in Issue 12 of ''The Dragon'' (February 1978) just prior to the book's release.<ref>{{cite journal | last = Norton| first = Andre | authorlink = Andre Norton | title = Quag's Keep (excerpts) | journal = The Dragon | issue = 12 | pages = 22\u201330 | publisher = [[TSR, Inc.|TSR]] | location = Lake Geneva WI |date=February 1978}}</ref> She and [[Jean Rabe]] were collaborating on the sequel to her 1979 [[Greyhawk]] novel ''Quag Keep'' when she died. ''Return to Quag Keep'' was completed by Rabe and published by [[Tor Books]] in January 2006.<ref name=\"isfdb\" />\n\nHer final complete novel, ''Three Hands for Scorpio'', was published on April 1, 2005. Besides ''Return to Quag Keep'', Tor has published two more novels with Norton and Rabe credited as co-authors, ''Dragon Mage'' (November 2006) and ''Taste of Magic'' (January 2008).<ref name=\"isfdb\" /> <!-- our bibliography and ISFDB suggest that a continuing project with Mercedes Lackey was cancelled -->\n\n===Series===\nNorton wrote more than a dozen [[speculative fiction]] series, but her longest, and longest-running project was \"[[Witch World]]\", which began with [[Witch World (novel)|the novel ''Witch World'']] in 1963. The first six novels were [[Ace Books]] [[paperback originals]] published from 1963 to 1968.<ref name=\"isfdb\" /> From the 1970s most of the series was published in hardcover editions.<ref name=\"isfdb\" /> From the 1980s some were written by Norton and a co-author, and others were anthologies of short fiction for which she was editor. (Witch World became a [[shared universe]].){{efn|name=mcconchie}} There were dozens of books in all.<ref name=\"Locus\" />\n\nThe five novels of The Cycle of Oak, Yew, Ash, and Rowan, ''To the King a Daughter'',  ''Knight or Knave'', ''A Crown Disowned'',  ''Dragon Blade'', and ''The Knight of the Red Beard'', were written with [[Sasha Miller]].<ref>Andre Norton and Sasha Miller (2008), ''The Knight of the Red Beard'', 2009 reprint, New York:  Tor, p. [2].</ref>  The fifth and last novel was dedicated \"To my late collaborator, Andre Norton, whose vision inspired the NordornLand cycle.\"<ref>Andre Norton and Sasha Miller (2008), ''The Knight of the Red Beard'', 2009 reprint, New York:  Tor, p. [7].</ref>  (\"NordornLand cycle\" is another name for this cycle.)\n\n==Legacy==\n[[File:Voodoo Planet, by Andrew North - cover - Project Gutenberg eText 18846.jpg|thumb|Cover of ''Voodoo Planet'' by Andrew North, artist Ed Valigursky; half of [[Ace Double]] #D-345 (1959)]]\n\nOn February 20, 2005, the [[Science Fiction and Fantasy Writers of America]], which had honored Norton with its [[Grand Master Nebula|Grand Master]] Award in 1984, announced the creation of the [[Andre Norton Award]], to be given each year for an outstanding work of fantasy or science fiction for the [[young adult literature]] market, beginning with 2005 publications. While the Norton Award is not a [[Nebula Award]], it is voted on by SFWA members on the Nebula ballot and shares some procedures with the Nebula Awards.<ref name=\"SFWA2012\" /><ref name=\"SFWAnorton\" /><ref name=\"SFAwards-nebula\" /> Nominally for a young adult book, actually the eligible class is middle grade and young adult novels.<!-- for one, Jenn Reese on the blog tour --> This added a category for genre fiction to be recognized and supported for young readers.<ref>KRISTIN L. PAULSON, Overcoming the Stigma of Science Fiction and Fantasty in the Classroom.2011 MA Thesis, University of Florida.</ref><ref>\nAN OVERVIEW OF THE ANDRE NORTON AWARD http://etd.fcla.edu/UF/UFE0043172/paulson_k.pdf</ref> Unlike Nebulas, there is a jury whose function is to expand the ballot beyond the six books with most nominations by members.<!-- page needed -->\n\nOften called the Grande Dame of Science Fiction and Fantasy by biographers such as J. M. Cornwell,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theroseandthornezine.com/Profile/andrenorton.html |title=An Interview with Andre Norton |publisher=Theroseandthornezine.com |accessdate=2011-12-22}}</ref> and organizations such as [[Science Fiction and Fantasy Writers of America]],<ref name=\"SFWA-norton\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sfwa.org/archive/news/anorton.htm |title=SFWA Biography|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091009032743/http://www.sfwa.org/archive/news/anorton.htm |archivedate=October 9, 2009 }}</ref> ''[[Publishers Weekly]]'',<ref>{{Cite book|title = Fiction Book Review: Warlock|author = Andre Norton|publisher = Author Baen Books|isbn = 978-0-671-31849-9|url = https://archive.org/details/warlock00nort|website = PublishersWeekly.com|accessdate = 2015-10-18|url-access = registration}}</ref> and ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'', Andre Norton wrote novels for over 70 years. She had a profound influence on the entire genre, having over 300 published titles read by at least four generations of science fiction and fantasy readers and writers. Notable authors who cite her influence include [[Greg Bear]], [[Lois McMaster Bujold]], [[C. J. Cherryh]], [[Cecilia Dart-Thornton]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dartthornton.com/about/about_interview2.html |title=Interview with Cecilia Dart-Thornton |publisher=Future Fiction |date=August 2001 |quote=Other authors who have influenced and inspired me (in no particular order), include Nicholas Stuart Gray, George McDonald, Andre Norton&nbsp;... |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130106040926/http://www.dartthornton.com/about/about_interview2.html |archive-date=2013-01-06 }}</ref> [[Tanya Huff]],<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Switzer |first1=David M|first2=James |last2=Schellenberg|date=October 1998|title=Wizards, Vampires & a Cat: From the Imagination of Tanya Huff|journal=Challenging Destiny|publisher=Crystalline Sphere Publishing|issue=4|url=http://www.challengingdestiny.com/interviews/huff.htm|quote=I'd have to say the two general influences are Andre Norton for an incredibly varied body of work that can be read and enjoyed by both adults and twelve year olds&nbsp;...}}</ref> [[Mercedes Lackey]], [[Charles de Lint]], [[Joan D. Vinge]], [[David Weber]], [[K. D. Wentworth]], and [[Catherine Asaro]].\n\n==High Hallack Library==\nThe High Hallack Library was a facility that Norton was instrumental in organizing and opening. Designed as a research facility for genre writers, and scholars of \"popular\" literature (the genres of science fiction, fantasy, mystery, western, romance, gothic, and horror), it was located near Norton's home in Murfreesboro, Tennessee.<ref name=\"norton\">{{cite web|url=http://www.andre-norton.org/highhallack/index.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130703173204/http://www.andre-norton.org/highhallack/index.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=2013-07-03 |title=High Hallack Genre Writers' Research and Reference Library |publisher=Andre-Norton.org }}, Retrieved 2013-5-31.</ref>\n\nThe facility, named after one of the continents in Norton's ''Witch World'' series, was home to over 10,000 texts, videos and various other media.  Attached to the facility were three guest rooms, allowing authors and scholars the chance to stay on-site to facilitate their research goals.<ref name=\"norton\" />\n\nThe facility was opened on February 28, 1999, and operated until March 2004.  Most of the collection was sold during the closing days of the facility.  The declining health of Andre Norton was one of the leading causes of its closing.<ref name=\"norton\" />\n\n==See also==\n* [[Andre Norton bibliography]]\n* [[:Category:Works by Andre Norton]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist |25em |notes=\n{{efn|name=mcconchie |1=\nRegarding ''The Duke's Ballad'' \"by Andre Norton and Lyn McConchie\", published in 2005, McConchie states \"Witch World setting, marketed as by Andre Norton and Lyn McConchie, although all writing and revision done by Lyn using Andre's background.\" And she says much the same for all four of their Witch World novels (1995 to 2005). \n<br />&nbsp;[http://www.lynmcconchie.com/new/?page_id=20 \"Lyn's Books\"]. [[Lyn McConchie]]. Last updated 2012-09-17. Retrieved 2013-05-02.\n}}\n{{efn|name=starred |1=\n''Kirkus'' reviewed only hardcover first editions; at the time, Norton had only recently published her first paperback original, ''The Crossroads of Time'' (Ace Double, 1956).\n}}\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist |25em |refs=\n<!-- vital refs -->\n<ref name=\"SSDI\">\n[https://familysearch.org/pal:/MM9.1.1/J5TG-CM2 Andre M Norton, \"United States Social Security Death Index\"]. \"United States Social Security Death Index\", index, FamilySearch, March 17, 2005. Retrieved 2013-02-12. Citing U.S. Social Security Administration, Death Master File, database (Alexandria, Virginia: National Technical Information Service, ongoing).</ref>\n<ref name=\"Lehmannhaupt\">\nChristopher Lehmann-Haupt, \"[https://www.nytimes.com/2005/03/18/books/18norton.html?_r=1 Andre Norton Dies at 93; a Master of Science Fiction\"], ''The New York Times'', March 18, 2005. Retrieved 2009-10-26.</ref>\n<ref name=\"Locus\">\n\"Andre Norton (1912\u20132005)\", [[Locus (magazine)|''Locus'']], April 2005, pp. 5, 65.</ref>\n<ref name=\"Mclellan\">\nDennis McLellan, \"[http://articles.latimes.com/2005/mar/19/local/me-norton19 Andre Norton, 93; A Prolific Science Fiction, Fantasy Author\"], ''Los Angeles Times'', March 19, 2005. Retrieved 2008-12-15.</ref>\n\n<!-- bibliog refs -->\n<ref name=\"isfdb\"><!-- instructs use of ISFDB --> \n{{isfdb name |209}} ('''ISFDB'''). Retrieved 2013-03-28. Select a title to see its linked publication history and general information. Select a particular edition (title) for more data at that level, such as a front cover image or linked contents.</ref>\n<ref name=isfdb-huon>\n[http://www.isfdb.org/cgi-bin/title.cgi?11103 \"Bibliography: Huon of the Horn\"]. ISFDB. Retrieved 2013-03-28.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"LCC\"><!-- instructs use of LCC -->\n{{cite web|url=http://lccn.loc.gov/n80126299|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151018040121/http://lccn.loc.gov/n80126299 |title=Norton, Andre|archivedate=October 18, 2015}} ''Library of Congress Authorities''. [[Library of Congress]]. Retrieved 2013-03-28.<br /> For LC catalog ('